<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName LSID="9A86501A-8F6C-59C1-A432-474489DCAE86" authority="W. H. Chen, Y. F. Han, J. D. Liang &amp; Z. Q. Liang" authorityName="W. H. Chen, Y. F. Han, J. D. Liang &amp; Z. Q. Liang" authorityYear="2022" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Neoaraneomyces" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Neoaraneomyces" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Neoaraneomyces W.H. Chen, Y.F. Han, J.D. Liang &amp; Z.Q. Liang</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="49">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Referring to a new genus parasitic on spiders</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. H. Chen, Y. F. Han, J. D. Liang &amp; Z. Q. Liang" authorityYear="2022" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Neoaraneomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Neoaraneomyces araneicola" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" rank="species" species="araneicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Neoaraneomyces araneicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
W.H. Chen, Y.F. Han, J.D. Liang &amp; Z.Q. Liang.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Colonies on PDA, white to grey, reverse yellowish. Conidiophores mononematous, usually arising from aerial hyphae, phialides solitary or in groups of two to three. Phialides emerging laterally from hyphae, forming a compact hymenium, abruptly narrowing into a neck. Conidia in chains, one-celled, hyaline, fusiform or ellipsoidal.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="host">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Host.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
Spider (
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Araneidae</taxonomicName>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Near roads and located on or under rocks.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="sexual morph">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Sexual morph.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
The genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lebert" authorityYear="1858" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Akanthomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Akanthomyces" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Akanthomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Beauveria" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Beauveria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Bionectriaceae" genus="Clonostachys" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Clonostachys" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Clonostachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Cordyceps" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cordyceps" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Cordyceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G.S.de Hoog" authorityYear="1978" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Engyodontium" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Engyodontium" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Engyodontium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
de Hoog, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cavara" authorityYear="1894" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Gibellula" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gibellula" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Gibellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora" authorityYear="2017" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Hevansia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ophiocordycipitaceae" genus="Hirsutella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hirsutella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Hirsutella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Petch" authorityYear="1931" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiocordycipitaceae" genus="Hymenostilbe" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hymenostilbe" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Hymenostilbe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W.Gams &amp; Zare" authorityYear="2001" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Lecanicillium" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecanicillium" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Lecanicillium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
W. Gams &amp; Zare, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Petch" authorityYear="1931" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiocordycipitaceae" genus="Ophiocordyceps" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ophiocordyceps" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Ophiocordyceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Petch, 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Purpureocillium" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Purpureocillium" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Purpureocillium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boudier" authorityYear="1885" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Torrubiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Torrubiella" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Torrubiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boud. have been reported as spider-pathogenic fungi in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boudier" authorityYear="1885" class="Sordariomycetes" genus="Torrubiella" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">Hypocreales</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11557-019-01512-3" author="Shrestha, B" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Progress" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" pagination="983 - 1003" refId="B21" refString="Shrestha, B, Kubatova, A, Tanaka, E, Oh, J, Yoon, DH, Sung, JM, Sung, GH, 2019. Spider-pathogenic fungi within Hypocreales (Ascomycota): Their current nomenclature, diversity, and distribution. Mycological Progress 18 (8): 983 - 1003, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s11557-019-01512-3" title="Spider-pathogenic fungi within Hypocreales (Ascomycota): Their current nomenclature, diversity, and distribution." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11557-019-01512-3" volume="18" year="2019">Shrestha et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cavara" authorityYear="1894" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Gibellula" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gibellula" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Gibellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only found on spiders. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. H. Chen, Y. F. Han, J. D. Liang &amp; Z. Q. Liang" authorityYear="2022" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Neoaraneomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Neoaraneomyces" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Neoaraneomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="Gibellua" lsidName="Gibellua" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Gibellua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its paecilomyces-like conidiogenous structures, phialides which were solitary or in groups of two to four, with fusiform to ellipsoidal conidia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
